00:00:00,320 --> 00:00:05,025
&gt;&gt; Styphnolobium japonicum or Japanese pagoda tree.

2
00:00:05,025 --> 00:00:09,949
This is a large round-headed tree that blooms late,

3
00:00:09,949 --> 00:00:14,739
generally in July or August, and white flowers.

4
00:00:14,740 --> 00:00:17,519
It's in the pea family and so there are bead

5
00:00:17,519 --> 00:00:20,564
like fruits that hang onto the tree after it flowers.

6
00:00:20,565 --> 00:00:23,609
It has green stems and compound leaves.

7
00:00:23,609 --> 00:00:27,309
Styphnolobium japonicum is a very drought-tolerant tree.

